<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Dungsummoner on 11-07-2000 10:57 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I agree with Muse...

Yes, there is a constant flow of people becoming 50+, but at the same time, there are new people playing EQ for the first time, and others who play low levels only.  I have a friend who is like this.

He plays the first 10 levels of a character he creates, then deletes them as his boredom with that character grows.  There are many people like this, I have met quite a few when I start new characters.  
So, while some people may like gaining level after level after level, eventually getting to 50+, many others enjoy being newbies and starting the whole world anew.  To keep these players happy, there should be added content for them, as well as added content for upper level players.  Besides, most of the people who play the game are not 50+, and I seriously doubt, on Lanys anyway, that they ever will outnumber 1-40's.  Hell, I have 4 characters myself, a 25th warrior, 14th druid, 20th ranger, and this one, Dungsummoner, a new necro (lvl 3).  I am trying to get all my characters to 30th, but it gets tedious camping the same old things and getting the same old loot in return.  Yes, Kunark was nice, but at the same time there are those who either don't have Kunark or don't want to go, so more Mid-lvl content should be added to the original Everquest.  I strongly dissagree with adding new material only for the high levels.  As an RPG, the game should be constantly changing for all characters, not merely a scarce few.  Perhaps increase the Orc population on Antonica and make raiding bands roam the zone.  Add new creatures in mid-lvl zones, such as Unrest.  For chrissakes, just make something new happen!</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
